  "text": "Some methodological issues should be addressed while dealing with the study results. As noted in the methods section, most of the tests were designed for the special needs of the current study. Those tests have not been validated prior to the current research, although post hoc, a relatively good reliability was found for most of the tests. The intervention programs were chosen also to accord with the literature both in Hebrew [CITATION_1] and Danish [CITATION_2] . The post intervention test results show that the intervention programs did enhance phonological and morphological awareness in a similar way that [CITATION_3] study in Danish had affected.",
